div.p:
The principal authorities for the life of Pausanias are Herodotus (ix. 10 sq.) and Thucydides (i. 94, 95, 128-134). There is a
                    biography of him by Cornelius Nepos. See also Diodorus, xi. 29- 34, 44-46;
                    Pausanias, iii. 4, 7 and⅛. 17, 7; Plutarch, Themistocles,
                    23; Id., Aristides, 11, 14-20, 23; Aristodemus, ii. iv.
                    vi.-viii. (in Müller’s Fragm. Hist. Graec., vol. v.);
                    Justin, 2, 14.
